<TITLE> Zimbabwe's MDC says runoff a bid to reverse vote </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 HARARE, April 5 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Zimbabwe's opposition Movement for Democratic Change said on Saturday the government of President Robert Mugabe would try to use a presidential runoff vote to reverse its defeat in elections. The MDC, which says it won last Saturday's presidential vote as well as its official victory in parliamentary polls, called on the United Nations, African Union and regional body SADC to intervene in Zimbabwe.
